# Whitelist approach: ignore everything by default, then un-ignore
# specifically what we want to sync. Safer than enumerating exclusions —
# new per-machine state added later won't accidentally get committed.

*

# Repo metadata
!.gitignore
!README.md

# Skill version
!VERSION

# Global commands (the closeout family + any other shared slash commands)
!commands/
!commands/*.md

# Reference docs read by the global skills
!docs/
!docs/*.md
